from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

pca = PCA(n_components=1)
    pca.fit(arr)
    evr = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
    plt.bar(np.arange(len(evr)), evr)
    plt.xticks(np.arange(len(evr)), [f"PC{i+1}" for i in range(len(evr))])
    plt.xlabel('Principal Components')
    plt.ylabel('Explained Variance Ratio')
    plt.title('Explained Variance Ratio of Principal Components')
    plt.show()
    return plt.gca()

pca = PCA(n_components=1)
    pca.fit_transform(arr)
    explained_variance = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
    print(explained_variance)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(np.arange(len(explained_variance)), explained_variance)
    ax.set_title("Explained Variance Ratio of Principal Components")
    ax.set_xlabel("Principal Component")
    ax.set_ylabel("Explained Variance Ratio")
    ax.set_ylim((0, 1.1))
    return ax

arr_sum = arr.sum(axis=0).reshape(1, -1)  # reshape the sum into a 2D array
    pca = PCA(n_components=1)  # create a PCA instance with n_components=1
    pca.fit(arr_sum)  # fit the PCA model
    evr = pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]  # get the explained variance ratio
    ax = plt.axes()
    ax.set_title("Explained Variance Ratio of Principal Components")
    ax.plot([1], [evr])  # plot the explained variance ratio
